Photo, History in Miniature -- During Nisei Week, an exhibit on Manzanar War 
Relocation Center, where Japanese-Americans were interned during World War II, 
is at Japanese Village Plaza in Little Tokyo. Robert Hasuike, top, spent 5,000 
hours building scale models. Among visitors to exhibit were Hatsumi Hino, 94, 
who lived at camp, and Dist. Atty. Ira Reiner and Bruce T. Kaji, president of 
Japanese American National Museum. CON KEYES / Los Angeles Times 
