Police believe Hartless was running after Butler in Southeast San Diego when 
Butler shot the officer in the forehead. Hartless, 24, was in a coma for three 
weeks before he died. 
</P>
<P>
The district attorney's office is seeking special circumstances in the case, 
making Butler eligible for the death penalty if he is convicted of first-degree 
murder. 
