<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: APPARENT VICTIM OF SEIZURE DIES IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aman who apparently suffered a seizure while driving died Tuesday when his van 
crashed into a tree in Thousand Oaks, the Ventura County Sheriff's Department 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
Reece James Vandergriff, 61, of Westlake Village was pronounced dead at 
Westlake Medical Center shortly after the 9:40 a.m. crash, Sgt. Herb Roper 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Vandergriff was driving south on Hampshire Road near Foothill Drive when he 
became incapacitated, Roper said. His van continued at about 20 m.p.h., 
traveling down a sidewalk for about 100 feet until it crashed into a tree at 
Hampshire and Townsgate roads. 
</P>
<P>
Roper said investigators examining Vandergriff's medical records determined 
that the man had a history of seizures. He said witnesses told deputies that 
the man appeared to be unconscious at the wheel. 
</P>
<P>
The type of seizure was unknown and will not be determined until an autopsy is 
performed later this week, Roper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
