<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: DANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bolshoi by any other spelling is still the Bolshoi. So the Bolshoi Theatre 
and its Western representative, the Entertainment Corp., have obtained an 
injunction in London against the "Bolschoi on Ice" tour scheduled for the 
United Kingdom and the United States later this year. An Entertainment Corp. 
executive said that "putting a c in the name makes no difference. . . . 
Bolshoi, however it may be spelt, is allied to one of the world's greatest 
ballet and opera companies" and has been misappropriated by the 3-year-old ice 
show. The Bolshoi Ballet, currently selling out at London's Coliseum and due to 
tour the U.S. next year, has no connection with the ice show. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
