<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nielsen Media Research on Tuesday signed a multimillion-dollar contract to 
develop a Latino ratings service with the two largest Spanish-language 
television operators, Univision Holdings Inc. and Telemundo Group Inc. 
Executives of the two companies said the Nielsen Latino ratings will help them 
attract spending by advertisers and agencies who in the past have been 
skeptical about the estimated size of the Spanish-language TV audience. The 
service will be tested this fall in Los Angeles area. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
