<P>
LELAND PLANE STILL MISSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ethiopian police and farmers with flashlights searched a remote mountain area 
overnight for the missing plane carrying Rep. Mickey Leland (D-Tex.) and 13 
other people. A daylong aerial search was suspended at dusk and will be resumed 
today. The Twin Otter aircraft disappeared Monday on its way from Addis Ababa 
to the Fugnido refugee camp near the border with Sudan, about 300 miles to the 
west. Leland, 44, has taken a keen interest in Africa's refugee problem. 
President Bush, saying Leland was on his sixth humanitarian mission in that 
part of the world, promised that his Administration will do all it can to help 
find the missing plane with Leland, eight other Americans and five Ethiopians. 
</P>
