High-Tech Firms Sign Licensing Pacts: Sun Microsystems Inc., which has licensed 
its semiconductor technology to Taiwanese and Japanese computer companies, has 
signed a license agreement with N.V. Philips of the Netherlands. Philips, the 
largest semiconductor manufacturer in Europe, will make 32-bit microprocessors 
