<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASTERN PILOTS VOTE TO CONTINUE THEIR STRIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eastern Airlines pilots meeting on Tuesday voted informally to continue 
supporting a continuation of their 5-month-old strike, union officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Air Line Pilots Assn. members meeting Tuesday in Newark, N.J., voted 203-15 in 
favor of sustaining the strike, union officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
