BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UTC Takes Unit Off Market: United Technologies Corp., Hartford, Conn., has 
taken its Norden Systems subsidiary off the market after more than a year of 
looking for a buyer willing to pay what UTC thought the radar-systems maker was 
worth, according to a letter to employees made public. UTC announced in April, 
1988, that it planned to sell Norden because it felt that Norden didn't fit 
into its overall plans and that it would fare better as part of a large defense 
electronics company. Norden, a $400-million-a-year company, makes radar systems 
for aircraft and ships. It also has a contract to make radar systems for the 
Federal Aviation Administration. 
