ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
SEOUL PUTS CONDITION ON GAME TALKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Korea said today that it will not reopen talks with North Korea on 
sending a joint team to the 1990 Beijing Asian Games unless Pyongyang stops 
hostile propaganda against the south. 
</P>
<P>
"Talks can only resume when North Korea proves it has stopped all political 
machinations to agitate the south," Seoul's chief delegate Chang Chung-sik said 
in response to an offer by Pyongyang on Tuesday to reopen the talks. 
</P>
<P>
The two Koreas, still technically at war, have agreed in principle to field a 
single team to the Beijing Games but have a host of details to fix. 
</P>
