<TEXT>
<P>
Saying he didn't hit anyone, Deion Sanders filed a counterclaim of assault 
against a fan he says was harassing his girlfriend during a minor league 
baseball game in Richmond, Va. 
</P>
<P>
Sanders, who plays with the New York Yankees' Columbus (Ohio) farm team in the 
International League and also is the Atlanta Falcons' first-round draft choice, 
was arrested Sunday on misdemeanor charges of assault for allegedly striking 
two fans. He denied hitting either man and said one of them took a gold chain 
from his girlfriend's neck. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred six days before Sanders was scheduled to go off probation 
in a battery and disorderly conduct case in Florida. His probation officer said 
he is considering whether to charge Sanders with violating the conditions of 
his probation. 
</P>
