</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Less than six months after saying he was trying to rid himself of drugs, George 
Gervin, the former pro basketball star, was arrested on charges of possession 
of marijuana and driving while intoxicated in San Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
Gervin, 37, was stopped after seen speeding and weaving on Interstate 410 in 
north-central San Antonio about 2:30 a.m. He was released on a personal 
recognizance bond shortly after 6 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Driving a black 1985 Porsche, Gervin was said to be traveling at 66 m.p.h. in a 
55-m.p.h. zone, according to sheriff's department reports. A substance believed 
to be marijuana was found in his possession, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the former National Basketball Assn. All-Star was treated 
for what police said was an apparent drug overdose. According to a police 
report in that February incident, Gervin said he snorted what he thought was 
cocaine, but later said he did not know what the substance was. 
</P>
