</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles White, formerly a running back with the Rams and USC, discussed his 
cocaine use at a California Commission on Drugs hearing in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
White said he was finally clean for the past nine months after years of nearly 
daily cocaine use. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought I was going to die; it got that bad one time," White testified. "I 
asked myself, 'When are you going to give in? When you've got a tag around your 
toe in the morgue?' " 
</P>
<P>
White, who has been working with other addicts at a Long Beach hospital, said 
it would be helpful for professional teams to have a recovered addict on staff 
to council players. 
</P>
<P>
The commission is gathering material for a report to state lawmakers. 
</P>
